stylometry:
Optimization is the desirable course of action to either cost minimize, or profit maximize.  This can be shown through queing lines, profit maximization tables and also linear programming models. 

The componenets of linear programming models are the objective function, constraints and the decision variables.  The objective function is the equation that will give the optimal outcome, again, either cost minimizing, or profit maximizing.  The decision variables are under the companies control, it's the numbers that they can change in order to figure out the optimal solution.  Finally, constraints can be called restrictions.
